---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import LoadingState from '../../components/LoadingState.astro';

const usageSnippet = `---
import { LoadingState } from 'comet-astro';

---

<div class="space-y-6">
  <LoadingState 
    label="Loading content…" 
    variant="default" 
    size="md"
    skeletonRows={3}
  />
</div>`;
---

<DocsLayout
  title="LoadingState"
  description="Accessible loading states with AAA contrast, multiple variants, and skeleton content."
>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      LoadingState provides a consistent way to display loading states across
      your application. It includes multiple variants from minimal inline
      loaders to full-screen overlays, all maintaining WCAG AAA contrast ratios
      and proper semantic markup.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Each variant includes proper ARIA labels and live regions so screen
      readers announce loading states appropriately. Skeleton content provides
      visual placeholders while maintaining accessibility best practices.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          label?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Loading message displayed to users and screen readers. Defaults to <code
            >"Loading…"</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          variant?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Visual style for the loading state. Choose <code>"default"</code>,
          <code>"minimal"</code>, <code>"card"</code>, or <code
            >"fullscreen"</code
          >. Defaults to <code>"default"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          size?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Adjusts spacing and text size. Options are <code>"sm"</code>,
          <code>"md"</code>, or <code>"lg"</code>. Defaults to <code>"md"</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          animation?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Spinner animation type. Choose <code>"spin"</code>, <code
            >"pulse"</code
          >,
          <code>"bounce"</code>, <code>"dots"</code>, <code>"bars"</code>, or
          <code>"orbit"</code>. Defaults to <code>"spin"</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          skeletonRows?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Number of skeleton placeholder rows to display. Maximum of 6 rows.
          Defaults to <code>0</code> (no skeleton content).
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          className?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Additional CSS classes to apply to the loading state container. Useful
          for custom positioning or spacing adjustments.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Import the component and configure the variant, size, and skeleton content
      to match your loading context. The component automatically handles
      accessibility and maintains proper contrast ratios in both light and dark
      themes.
    </p>
    <pre
      class="overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-slate-700/70 bg-slate-950/80 p-4 text-sm text-slate-50 shadow-inner">
      <code class="language-astro">{usageSnippet}</code>
    </pre>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Variants</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-200">Default</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Centered loading state with spinner and label
        </p>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-6">
          <LoadingState label="Loading content…" variant="default" size="md" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-200">Minimal</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Inline loading state for smaller spaces
        </p>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-6">
          <LoadingState label="Loading…" variant="minimal" size="sm" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-200">Card</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">Loading state with card background</p>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-6">
          <LoadingState
            label="Processing data…"
            variant="card"
            size="md"
            skeletonRows={2}
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Sizes</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-8">
        <div class="w-32 text-sm text-slate-300">Small</div>
        <LoadingState label="Loading…" variant="minimal" size="sm" />
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-8">
        <div class="w-32 text-sm text-slate-300">Medium</div>
        <LoadingState label="Loading…" variant="minimal" size="md" />
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-8">
        <div class="w-32 text-sm text-slate-300">Large</div>
        <LoadingState label="Loading…" variant="minimal" size="lg" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">With Skeleton Content</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Add skeleton rows to provide visual placeholders while content loads.
      Skeleton rows automatically adjust their size based on the component size.
    </p>
    <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-6">
      <LoadingState
        label="Loading article…"
        variant="default"
        size="md"
        skeletonRows={4}
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-8">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Animation Types</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Choose from different animation styles to match your design preferences.
      All animations respect the user's reduced motion preferences.
    </p>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-4 text-center"
      >
        <LoadingState label="Spin" variant="minimal" animation="spin" />
      </div>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-4 text-center"
      >
        <LoadingState label="Pulse" variant="minimal" animation="pulse" />
      </div>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-4 text-center"
      >
        <LoadingState label="Dots" variant="minimal" animation="dots" />
      </div>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg border border-slate-700 bg-slate-800/50 p-4 text-center"
      >
        <LoadingState label="Bars" variant="minimal" animation="bars" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-4">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      LoadingState uses semantic markup with proper ARIA labels and live regions
      to announce loading states to screen readers. Contrast ratios exceed WCAG
      AAA requirements (7:1+) in both light and dark themes.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      All animations respect the <code>prefers-reduced-motion</code> setting, providing
      static alternatives for users who prefer reduced animation. Skeleton content
      uses neutral colors to avoid drawing attention while maintaining sufficient
      contrast for visibility.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      Use descriptive labels that clearly communicate what is being loaded, such
      as "Loading user profile" instead of generic "Loading" text. The
      fullscreen variant automatically traps focus and provides proper backdrop
      semantics.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
